05/01/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- The chairman of the opposition Democratic Party, Sali Berisha, said Saturday (4 January) that the agreement with the ruling Socialist party is not being observed.
His statement referred to the recent victory of Socialist candidate Valentine Leskaj in a parliamentary race in Elbasan.
Berisha says procedures in that election were irregular.
However, he also said the opposition is determined to observe the agreement, which aims to guarantee the rule of law and democracy in Albania.
(ATA - 04/01/03)
